{{Infobox museum | name = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = Seychelles Natural History Museum Front.JPG | imagesize = 250px | caption = | alt = Sculpture outside the Natural History Museum | map_type = | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | map_dot_label = | former_name = | established = 1964 | dissolved = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | location = Victoria, Mahé, Seychelles | coordinates = {{Coord|-4.623|55.453|type:landmark_region:SC|display=inline,title}} | type = | accreditation = | key_holdings = | collections = | collection_size = | visitors = | founder = | director = | president = | chairperson = | curator = | historian = | owner = | publictransit = | car_park = | parking = | network = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | embedded = }}
The '''Seychelles Natural History Museum''' is a [[natural history museum]] in the [[Seychelles]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.africa.com/seychelles/museums/#a12 | title=Museums in Seychelles | publisher=Africa.com | accessdate=9 August 2014 }}</ref>
The museum is located in next to the main post office in [[Victoria, Seychelles|Victoria]], the capital of the Seychelles, on [[Mahé Island]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ernesta|first1=Sharon|last2=Bonnelame|first2=Betymie|title=Seychelles’ history museum gets a facelift, to open end of 2017|url=http://www.seychellesnewsagency.com/articles/7098/Seychelles+history+museum+gets+a+facelift%2C+to+open+end+of+|website=Seychelles News Agency|accessdate=1 October 2017|date=15 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/Attraction_Review-g298572-d480551-Reviews-Seychelles_Natural_History_Museum-Victoria_Mahe_Island.html | title=Seychelles Natural History Museum | publisher=[[TripAdvisor]] | accessdate=9 August 2014 }}</ref>
The displays include sections on botany, zoology, geology and anthropology. There are also some items related to the history of the Seychelles People's Militia, the Seychelles People's Liberation Army and the [[Seychelles People's Defence Forces]].
